This paper deals with committee selection rules, which are often studied in the field of computational social choice (cs.GT). The use of local search to approximately maximize the PAV score suggests a focus on algorithmic techniques, which is also a common theme in cs.AI and cs.DS. The concept of cohesive groups of voters is relevant to both cs.LG (learning theory) and cs.SI (social and information networks).
